1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,300
The story of Arthur the Rat. Once upon a time there was a young rat who couldn't

2
00:00:06,300 --> 00:00:11,660
make up his mind. Whenever the other rat says to him if he would like to come out

3
00:00:11,660 --> 00:00:14,980
hunting with them, he would answer in a hoarse voice.

4
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:22,040
I don't know and when they said would you rather stay inside? He would say yes or

5
00:00:23,080 --> 00:00:25,220
No, either he'd always

6
00:00:25,600 --> 00:00:28,000
Shake making your choice

7
00:00:28,500 --> 00:00:29,980
one fine day

8
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:31,940
His Aunt Josephine said to him,

9
00:00:32,320 --> 00:00:36,500
Now look here, no one will ever care for you if you carry on like this.

10
00:00:37,020 --> 00:00:40,300
You have no more mind of your own than a greasy old blade of grass.

11
00:00:41,160 --> 00:00:44,040
The young rat coughed and looked quiet as usual, but said nothing.

12
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:52,580
think so," said his aunt, stamping her foot, for she couldn't bear to see the young rat

13
00:00:52,580 --> 00:00:59,820
so cold-blooded. I don't know was all he ever answered, and then he walked off to

14
00:00:59,820 --> 00:00:59,980
think.

15
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:08,920
for an hour or more. Rather he would stay in his hole in the ground or go out into the loft.

16
00:01:09,660 --> 00:01:14,980
One night the rats heard a loud noise in the loft. It was a very dreary old clock.

17
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:19,640
The roof let the rain come down, come washing in.

18
00:01:20,140 --> 00:01:25,900
The beams and the rafters had all rotted through, so the whole thing was quite unsafe.

19
00:01:26,760 --> 00:01:29,580
At last, one of the joists gave way.

20
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:33,440
and the beams fell with one edge on the floor.

21
00:01:36,040 --> 00:01:39,500
The walls shook, the cupola fell off,

22
00:01:39,880 --> 00:01:44,200
and all the rats' hair stood on end with fear and horror.

23
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:53,560
This won't do, said the leader, we can't stay cooped up here any longer, so they sent out scouts to search for a new home.

24
00:01:54,760 --> 00:01:59,720
A little later on that evening, the scouts come back and said they had found an old-fashioned horse farm.

25
00:02:00,620 --> 00:02:03,460
where there would be room for all of them.

26
00:02:03,600 --> 00:02:05,200
The leader gave the order at once,

27
00:02:05,500 --> 00:02:06,460
come you fallen in.

28
00:02:06,760 --> 00:02:08,760
And the rats crawled out of the hole right away

29
00:02:08,760 --> 00:02:10,880
and stood on the floor in a long line.

30
00:02:11,820 --> 00:02:14,520
Just then the old rat caught sight of young Arthur.

31
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:16,700
That was the name of the shaker.

32
00:02:17,120 --> 00:02:22,000
He wasn't in the line, and he wasn't exactly outside it.

33
00:02:22,420 --> 00:02:24,580
He stood just by it.

34
00:02:25,040 --> 00:02:29,980
Come on, get in line, growled the old rat coarsely.

35
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:38,140
Of course you're coming too. I don't know, said Arthur calmly, why the idea of it.

36
00:02:38,180 --> 00:02:41,640
You don't think it's safe here anymore, do you?

37
00:02:41,980 --> 00:02:44,980
I'm not certain, said Arthur undaunted.

38
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:47,840
The roof may not fall down yet.

39
00:02:48,900 --> 00:02:52,840
Well, said the old rat, you can't wait for you to join us.

40
00:02:53,040 --> 00:02:56,420
Then he turned to the other and shouted, right about the face, march.

41
00:02:57,120 --> 00:02:59,360
And the long line marched out.

42
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:06,380
born while a young rat watched him. I think I'll go tomorrow, he said to himself, but then again

43
00:03:06,380 --> 00:03:14,700
perhaps I won't. It's so nice and snug here. I guess I'll go back to my hole under the log for a while.

44
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:20,540
just to make up my mind, but during the night there was a big crash.

45
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:24,200
Down came beams, rafters, joists, the whole business.

46
00:03:25,040 --> 00:03:29,440
Next morning, it was a foggy day, some men came to look over the damage.

47
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:35,000
It seemed odd to them that the old building was not haunted by rats, but at last one of

48
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:40,420
them happened to move aboard, and he caught sight of a young rat, quite dead, half in

49
00:03:40,420 --> 00:03:41,540
and half out of his hole.

50
00:03:42,300 --> 00:03:44,980
Thus, the shirker got his due, and there was no more.

51
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:45,840
morning for him.

